{"title":"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST Project Bike Rethinks All-Mountain in Sleek Ivory & Chrome","link":"https://bikerumor.com/dangerholm-scott-genius-st-project-bike-rethinks-all-mountain-in-sleek-ivory-chrome/","date":1710280180000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_photos-by-GUSTAV-GULLHOLM-800x533.jpg\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, angled\" /></p>\n<p>Serial bike customizer Gustav Gullholm <em>aka</em> Dangerholm is back with another concept bike project, this time reimagining Scott’s latest <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2023-scott-genius-mountain-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Genius ST</a> as the future of all-mountain bikes. No visible cables, wires, or suspension. An upside-down fork and the return of chromed-out wheels. My only reservation is the likely extra weight of all that sand-colored creamy Ivory paint, when it could have been raw carbon. Oh Dangerholm, what has become of your weight weenie ways?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Scott Genius ST x Dangerholm all-mountain bike of the future?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-view.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"2000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-view.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-view.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-view-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-view-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-view-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-view-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-view-1536x1536.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos by Gustav Gullholm/Scott)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Swedish bike tweaker Dangerholm’s latest custom MTB project is “his vision of how the mountain bike of the future might look”. Starting with the already <em>bold</em>ly futuristic <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-scott-genius-is-a-highly-adaptable-trail-bike-for-big-mountain-days/\" target=\"_blank\">Genius Super Trail</a>, Dangerholm built one of the sleekest trail bikes ever. 150mm of 29er rear wheel travel – with 3 ride-proven Open-Traction-Climb compression &amp; travel lock-out settings – paired to 160mm of travel up front.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, rear end details\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_angled-rear-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Will the future of mountain bikes hide all shocks inside the frame? Will they hide brake lines in the bars, too? Everything routed through the headset, really? Tiny Zirbel thumb shifters &amp; dropper remotes that almost disappear into the grip lock-rings. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, cockpit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_integrated-cockpit-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, there will be more wireless electronic components, but I can only hope some of those bulky batteries might get hidden too. I think we also aren’t going to be able to avoid the one-piece cockpits that are trying to make separate bar &amp; stems a thing of the past. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Futuristic standards?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, Trickstuff brake\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Trickstuff-brakes-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A few welcome changes have become the modern norm. Long travel dropper seatposts. Lightweight 4-piston brakes. And an actually universal derailleur mounting standard.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, TacLoc downtube shifter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_downtube-shifter-tracloc-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I’m not so sure if there will be a resurgence of bar-end/downtube shifters to actuate various shock lock-out modes. But who am I to say for sure? Ceramic bearings and Solid Lube Tech bearings anywhere possible are surely here to stay.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_rear-wheel.jpg\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_rear-wheel.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, silver rear wheel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_rear-wheel.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_rear-wheel-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_rear-wheel-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_rear-wheel-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_rear-wheel-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_rear-wheel-1536x1536.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-wheel.jpg\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-wheel.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, chrome front wheel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-wheel.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-wheel-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-wheel-800x800.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-wheel-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-wheel-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_front-wheel-1536x1536.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>At least we can all hope that the future of mountain bikes will see the return of more shiny silver (alloy) wheels and spokes. Everything always in matte black on black is getting a bit stale, am I right? </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Super custom details!</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Hopp-Carbon-CeramicSpeed-derailleur-tuning.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Hopp-Carbon-CeramicSpeed-derailleur-tuning.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, Hopp-ed up deailleur\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Hopp-Carbon-CeramicSpeed-derailleur-tuning.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Hopp-Carbon-CeramicSpeed-derailleur-tuning-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Hopp-Carbon-CeramicSpeed-derailleur-tuning-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Hopp-Carbon-CeramicSpeed-derailleur-tuning-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Hopp-Carbon-CeramicSpeed-derailleur-tuning-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_Hopp-Carbon-CeramicSpeed-derailleur-tuning-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On an otherwise reasonable custom build… well, except for the lust-worthy Intend Hero upside-down fork and hard-to-get Trickstuff Piccola HD brakes! Dangerholm still manages to sneak some silly over-the-top upgrades in there, too. As if a SRAM X0 T-type derailleur wasn’t fancy enough, this one has several of its modular alloy elements replaced with custom Hopp Carbon upgrades. And of course a CeramicSpeed OSPW X cage upgrade for improved aerodynamics and reduced drag. Why not, when money is no object?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_custom-chainring.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_custom-chainring.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, chainring\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_custom-chainring.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_custom-chainring-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_custom-chainring-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_custom-chainring-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_custom-chainring-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_custom-chainring-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>He also sneaks in a new Dangerholm-branded 1x machined RadoxX chainring that is being sold through his r2-bike.com online retailer partner. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, titanium brake bolts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_METI-titanium-brake-bolts-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And custom-made, but now commercially available, ultralight METI titanium brake bolts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_in-creamy-ivory.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_in-creamy-ivory.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, front end\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_in-creamy-ivory.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_in-creamy-ivory-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_in-creamy-ivory-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_in-creamy-ivory-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_in-creamy-ivory-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_in-creamy-ivory-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>My weight-conscious sensibilities are a bit worried about all that extra paint, though. We all know that it takes more light-colored paint to cover up the dark raw black carbon fiber. So maybe there’s some justification to still going super stealth with our custom bike builds after all!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Complete Build Spec:</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_complete.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_complete.jpg\" alt=\"Dangerholm Scott Genius ST custom all-mountain bike of the future project, complete\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_complete.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_complete-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_complete-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_complete-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_complete-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Dangerholm-Scott-Genius-ST-custom-all-mountain-bike-of-the-future-project_complete-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Frame: SCOTT Genius ST size L 150mm travel<br />Paint color: RAL 1014 Ivory<br />Thru-axle: METI titanium<br />Rear shock: Fox Float X NUDE<br />Remote: Customized frame-mounted 10-speed shifter<br />Fork: Intend Hero 160mm travel with METI titanium axle<br />Headset: Syncros with CeramicSpeed SLT bearings<br />Top cap: RadoxX x Dangerholm Oknytt<br />Handlebar: Syncros Hixon iC SL Rise 50mm virtual stem<br />Grips: Syncros AM size M<br />Controllers: Zirbel Twister WE03 connected to SRAM BlipBox<br />Rear derailleur: SRAM Eagle AXS X0 Transmission with Hopp Carbon Parts tuning<br />Rear derailleur cage: CeramicSpeed OSPW X for Transmission<br />Cassette: SRAM X0 Transmission<br />Chain: SRAM X0 Transmission<br />Crankset: SRAM X0 Transmission<br />Chainring: RadoxX x Dangerholm Bergakungen 34T<br />Bottom bracket: CeramicSpeed DUB Coated<br />Preload adjuster: CeramicSpeed DUB<br />Pedals: Xpedo Baldwin<br />Brakes: Trickstuff Piccola HD<br />Brake discs: Trickstuff Dächle UL 180mm+203mm<br />Brake bolts: METI titanium<br />Saddle: Syncros Tofino SL<br />Seat post: RockShox Reverb AXS 170mm<br />Seat post clamp: Intend Corona<br />Hubs: DUKE Bad Boy<br />Spokes: Sapim CX-Ray<br />Rims: DUKE Fury Star 6ters custom polished<br />Front tire: Maxxis Assegai EXO+ MaxxGrip 2,5”<br />Rear tire: Maxxis Assegai EXO+ MaxxTerra 2,5”<br />Tubeless sealant: Syncros Eco Sealant<br />Valves: Damoff<br />Weight with pedals: 13.60kg / 29.98lbs</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.scott-sports.com/global/en/products/bike-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Scott-Sports.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/dangerholm-scott-genius-st-project-bike-rethinks-all-mountain-in-sleek-ivory-chrome/\">Dangerholm Scott Genius ST Project Bike Rethinks All-Mountain in Sleek Ivory &amp; Chrome</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"5386f1099de7fa36ebef20ff76e04b0950dfd35137746fb4bc840e5d7e31b16a","category":"Cycling"}